http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Direct-train-from-Kalaburagi-to-Hyderabad-from-Jan.-6/article13977846.ece

Central Railways has decided to begin a direct train service from Kalaburagi station to Hyderabad from January 6. According to the sources in Central Railways, the train will be run as a special train upto January 31 and a decision on continuing it will be taken after that.The former Railway Minister M. Mallikarjun Kharge had announced the introduction of the train but it could not be realised due to the absence of a pitlane at Kalaburagi station.According to Senior Divisional Commercial Manager of Central Railways K.V. Thomas, the train has been given the number 01317/01318.The train will leave Kalaburagi at 10.15 a.m. and reach Hyderabad at 2.50 p.m. On its return, the train will leave Hyderabad at 4 p.m. and reach Kalaburagi at 9 p.m.